http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/Tyagaraya-Aradhanotsavams/article14025991.ece

The annual Sri Tyagaraya Aradhanotsavams organised by Sri Raja Rajeshwara Swamy Devasthanam in Vemulawada got off to a start on a traditional note on Thursday.Vemulawada legislator Ch Ramesh Babu performed traditional puja to launch the musical festivities by offering floral tributes to the portrait of Tyagaraja. The musical festival would be conducted till February 1. During the inaugural ceremony on Thursday, eminent playback singer P Susheela participated in the celebrations. She visited the temple shrine and offered prayers to the presiding deities. Music lovers had attended in large numbers to the listen to the classical numbers sung by P Susheela.